==Introduction==
A '''Portal Column Layout''' renders group of components in one single column which is embedded in the Portal Layout cell:


==Definition==
<pre>
<concept>
  <structure layout="portal">
    <group name="A">                            <!-- first row -->
      <group name="column"layout="portalcolumn">  <!-- column children will be rendered as singe column -->
        <group name="1">                          <!-- first Portal Box in first row-->
          <property name="Property A.1.a">
          <property name="Property A.1.b">
          <property name="Property A.1.c">
        </group>
        <group name="2">                          <!-- second Portal Box in first row-->
          <property name="Property A.2.a">
          <property name="Property A.2.b">
          <property name="Property A.2.c">
        </group>
      </group>
      <group name="3">
        <property name="Property B.1.a">
        <property name="Property B.1.b">
        <property name="Property B.1.c">
      </group>
    </group>
    <group name="B">                           <!-- second row  -->
      <group name="1">                         <!-- first Portal Box in second row-->
        <property name="Property B.1.a">
        <property name="Property B.1.b">
        <property name="Property B.1.c">
      </group>
      <group name="2">                        <!-- second Portal Box in second row-->
        <property name="Property B.2.a">
        <property name="Property B.2.b">
        <property name="Property B.2.c">
      </group>
    </group>
  <structure>
</concept>
</pre>
